<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861222-0159 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Monarch Capital Corp.</HL><DD> 12/22/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MONBOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><TEXT>   MONARCH CAPITAL CORP. said it is offering $40 million of 14% non-recourse notes due 1991. Proceeds from the notes, priced at par, will be used to finance the company's previously announced acquisitions of Narragansett Capital Corp. and Narragansett Venture Corp. Non-recourse notes are secured by the assets of an acquired company, not those of the issuer. Buyers of Monarch Capital's non-recourse notes may seek repayment only from the assets of Narragansett Capital and Narragansett Venture. Morgan Stanley andamp; Co. is the underwriter. Monarch is based in Springfield, Mass. </TEXT></DOC>